\nbecomes harder to constrain these parameters. In the second scenario, we\nanalyze the achievable constraints on primordial features when two of the\nastrophysical parameters, namely, minimum halo mass and ionizing efficiency are\nuncertain. We find that the effect of the bump on the shape and the amplitude\nof the 21 cm power spectrum is distinct from the impact of varying the\nastrophysical parameters, and hence they may potentially be distinguished.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Dec 2022 19:04:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Jun 2023 05:03:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-07"}
