ry disks, the abundances of amorphous silicates and gases have\nwidely been considered to be a primary property. However, our study suggests\nthat impact processing may play a significant role in generating secondary\namorphous silicates and gases in those disks. Infrared spectra of the shocked\nMurchison samples are also suggesting that the comets also contain shocked\nMurchison-like material.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Dec 2022 10:07:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-02"}
